artifacts.summary: Research on proving decide_complete theorem, analyzing gap between tableau completeness and proof extraction

findings_summary: The decide_complete theorem requires bridging tableau_complete (Task 624) with proof extraction. The main challenge is that buildTableau returning allClosed does not directly produce a DerivationTree proof term - the decide function may still return timeout if proof extraction fails. Three approaches identified: (1) bridge with sorry placeholder, (2) strengthen proof extraction to reconstruct proofs from closure reasons, (3) weaken statement to avoid explicit proof term.
